count 1 to N

in dp to store not of bits
    count_ones(n) = count_ones(n // 2) + (n % 2)

This means:
    The count of 1s in n =
        (count of 1s in half of n) + (1 if n is odd, else 0)    
    So as numbers double, the pattern repeats and extends by 1 bit.



set Bit      n                    (1 << i)
clear Bit    n &= ~(1 << i)       set the ith bit to 0
Toggle bit   n ^= (1 << i)        Flip the i-th bit is 1
